kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of obtaining thine approval:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil speech does not ascend to Thee."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Nh, L.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ar~N", "text_ar": "شَرٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Poverty."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fever."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b4-  It is also an epithet, applied to a man, (Yoo, S,) and so is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ariyrN", "text_ar": "شَرِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Akh, S, A, Msb, K,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Evil, wrongdoing, unjust, bad, corrupt, wicked, mischievous, vitious,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "depraved:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Yoo, * Akh, * S, * A, * Msb, K: *) [fem. of the former"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ar~apN", "text_ar": "شَرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xayorapN", "text_ar": "خَيْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is fem. of its contr."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xayorN", "text_ar": "خَيْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ur~aY", "text_ar": "شُرَّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", fem. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$ar~u", "text_ar": "اَشَرُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", is used in the same sense, as will be shown in what follows:] the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ar~N", "text_ar": "شَرٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Yoo, S,) or of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ariyrN", "text_ar": "شَرِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Akh, S, Msb, K,) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oraArN", "text_ar": "اَشْرَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Yoo, Akh, S, 